##  ** Other Information **

At UQ we know that our greatest strengths come from our diverse mix of
colleagues, this is reflected in our ongoing commitment to creating an
environment focused on [ equity, diversity and inclusion
](https://staff.uq.edu.au/information-and-services/human-resources/diversity)
. We ensure that we are always attracting, retaining and promoting colleagues
who are representative of the diversity in the broader community, whether that
be [ gender identity ](https://staff.uq.edu.au/information-and-services/human-
resources/diversity/gender) , [ LGBTQIA+
](https://staff.uq.edu.au/information-and-services/human-
resources/diversity/sexuality) , [ cultural and/or linguistic
](https://staff.uq.edu.au/information-and-services/human-
resources/diversity/cultural-linguistic) , [ Aboriginal and/or Torres Strait
Islander peoples ](https://staff.uq.edu.au/information-and-services/human-
resources/diversity/aboriginal-torres-strait-islanders) , or [ people with a
disability ](https://staff.uq.edu.au/information-and-services/human-
resources/diversity/disability) . Accessibility requirements and/or
adjustments can be directed to [ [email protected]  ](/cdn-cgi/l/email-
protection#87f3e6ebe2e9f3c7f2f6a9e2e3f2a9e6f2) .  
  
If you are a current employee (including casual staff and HDR scholars) or
hold an unpaid/affiliate appointment, please login to your staff [ Workday
account ](https://wd3.myworkday.com/uq/d/task/3005$4482.htmld) and visit the
internal careers board to apply for this opportunity. Please do NOT apply via
the external job board.  
  
** Applications close 3 April 2024 at 11.00pm AEST (R-35375). ** Applicants invited for interview will be asked to present a shortened undergraduate-level mock lecture and a research seminar on the afternoons (local Brisbane time) of ** April 30 & 1 May ** as part of the selection process. Please note that interviews have been scheduled for ** 2 May 2024. **   

